The paper discusses the performance of a cellular network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The analysis of the optimal tradeoff between performance gain and network cost involves system optimization (cs.SY) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the use of a stochastic-geometry model suggests a possible connection to probability and statistics (cs.PF).
